This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with optimizing the performance of a network of MEC-enabled base stations. It could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as the algorithm presented works in a distributed manner. The paper also deals with system optimization, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses optimization techniques, which could place it in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with load balancing, which could place it in the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
